{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-blog-post-js","path":"/how-to-fix-mysql-denied-for-user-root-localhost/","webpackCompilationHash":"74e08bd1f829f53045fc","result":{"data":{"site":{"siteMetadata":{"title":"Codycrunch","author":"NicoAudy"}},"markdownRemark":{"id":"d0421ac7-cc39-5371-a49a-46025e96e4d8","html":"<hr>\n<p>Start the MySQL server instance or daemon with the <code class=\"language-text\">--skip-grant-tables</code> option (security setting).</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"bash\"><pre class=\"language-bash\"><code class=\"language-bash\">$ mysqld --skip-grant-tables</code></pre></div>\n<p>Execute these statements.</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"bash\"><pre class=\"language-bash\"><code class=\"language-bash\">$ mysql -u root mysql\n$ mysql<span class=\"token operator\">></span> UPDATE user SET Password<span class=\"token operator\">=</span>PASSWORD<span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token string\">'my_password'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> where USER<span class=\"token operator\">=</span><span class=\"token string\">'root'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n$ mysql<span class=\"token operator\">></span> FLUSH PRIVILEGES<span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span></code></pre></div>\n<p>If you face the unknown field Password error above use:</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"text\"><pre class=\"language-text\"><code class=\"language-text\">update user set authentication_string=password(&#39;my_password&#39;) where user=&#39;root&#39;;</code></pre></div>\n<p>Finally, restart the instance/daemon without the <code class=\"language-text\">--skip-grant-tables</code> option.</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"bash\"><pre class=\"language-bash\"><code class=\"language-bash\">$ /etc/init.d/mysql restart</code></pre></div>\n<p>You should now be able to connect with your new password.</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"bash\"><pre class=\"language-bash\"><code class=\"language-bash\">$ mysql -u root -p</code></pre></div>\n<p>Enter password: <code class=\"language-text\">my_password</code></p>\n<p><img src=\"https://media.giphy.com/media/My6uWnBRiQrVC/giphy.gif\"></p>","timeToRead":1,"frontmatter":{"title":"How To Fix MySQL Denied For User Root Localhost","date":"April 03, 2019","spoiler":"Pengalaman pribadi saya setelah install MySQL untuk pertama kali terdapat error mysql denied, so here how to fix"},"fields":{"slug":"/how-to-fix-mysql-denied-for-user-root-localhost/","langKey":"en"}}},"pageContext":{"isCreatedByStatefulCreatePages":false,"slug":"/how-to-fix-mysql-denied-for-user-root-localhost/","previous":{"fields":{"slug":"/provide-server-to-https-using-lets-encrypt-and-nginx/","langKey":"en","directoryName":"provide-server-to-https-using-lets-encrypt-and-nginx","maybeAbsoluteLinks":[]},"frontmatter":{"title":"Provide Server To Https Using Let's Encrypt And Nginx"}},"next":{"fields":{"slug":"/using-single-action-classes-in-controller/","langKey":"en","directoryName":"using-single-action-classes-in-controller","maybeAbsoluteLinks":[]},"frontmatter":{"title":"Using Single Action Classes in Controller"}},"translations":[],"translatedLinks":[]}}}